1.3 "Integrated"
A form of implementation where PASSWORD TRANSFER is combined with the host application's user interface, workflows, or build system such that it functions as part of the larger application.

1.4 "Standalone"
A product or service whose primary functionality, marketed purpose, or user-facing capability is substantially provided by PASSWORD TRANSFER or by code derived from it. A work is considered Standalone when its core purpose, architecture, or user-facing functionality substantially derives from PASSWORD TRANSFER.

1.5 "Derivative Work"
As defined under applicable copyright law, including any work based upon or derived from the PASSWORD TRANSFER source code, including modifications, translations, extensions, or adaptations.

1.6 "Larger Work"
A combined distribution containing PASSWORD TRANSFER together with other separate and independent works. If PASSWORD TRANSFER could be removed from the Larger Work and the Larger Work would still be functional and useful, it is considered part of a Larger Work.

1.7 "Distribution"
Any transfer, publication, granting of access, or making available the software or its functionality to third parties.

1.8 "Source Code"
The preferred form for making modifications to the program, including build scripts and documentation necessary to produce and run the work.

